dct_title_s: Prof. G. Hirschfeld's archælogische reiseroute im südwestlichen Kleinasien 1874 / G. Hirschfeld
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by hachures. Red dots indicates ancient sites. Ruins sites names are given in Greek translation. Red and dotted lines indicate the routes explored  by G. Hirschfekd and H. Eggert (architect); black dotted line H. Kiepert route Tafel VI. Original map is filed in the Map/Geospatial Center, a map reproduction is attached to companion volume.
